  "title": "EV Business Operations Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the Role</strong></p><p>We’re looking for an experienced <strong>EV (Electric Vehicle) Business Operations Executive</strong> to support our Business Development/ Operations team. This role involves coordinating with the EV Charging operations team, analyzing performance data, and supporting the implementation of EV Charging initiatives across our sites. The ideal candidate will have strong analytical skills, a solid understanding of EV systems, and a passion for sustainable mobility.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>This role reports to the Business Development GM.</li><li>Collect, analyze, and interpret EV Charging performance and usage data to identify trends, issues, and opportunities.</li><li>Prepare data reports and presentations for management review, highlighting cost and usage trends.</li><li>Monitor EV Charging system performance, maintenance schedules in collaboration with technical and field teams.</li><li>Compile customer feedback to hardware and applications.</li><li>Support day-to-day activities with the EV Operations team to ensure smooth running of EV Charging and deployment operations and vendor coordination.</li><li>Review contracts, service agreements, and operational reports related to EV Charging operations and service providers.</li><li>Liaise with cross-functional teams to align on project goals and timelines.</li><li>Keep up-to-date with EV industry trends, technology updates, and government initiatives related to electrification.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Engineering, Environmental Studies, Business, Data Analytics, or related field.</li><li>Minimum 1 year Experience in EV industry, operations, fleet management, or sustainability projects.</li><li>Good understanding of EV Charging infrastructure, charging systems, and implementation processes.</li><li>Excellent coordination, communication, and problem-solving skills.</li><li>Able to work independently and manage multiple priorities in a fast-paced environment.</li></ul>",
